Matter Dichotomy 


The interesting point with the RST dynamics is now that it subdivides the configuration space of matter (i.e. the space of regular -matrices) into two dynamically separated subsets: the positive and negative mixtures, with the pure states appearing as an asymptotic limit of both kinds of mixtures. Here the criterium of membership refers to the determinant  of the intensity matrix  such that for  one has a "positive" ("negative") mixture. On the other hand the pure states are uniquely characterized by the well-known Fierz identity  for the intensity matrix, i.e.
 
