which actually identifies the effective localization fields  as gradient fields
 
in agreement with the claim ().

Once the transition from the localization fields  to the amplitude fields  () has been made, one will not be satisfied with transcribing the abstract conservation equation () to the localization field  (or , resp.) but one will readily proceed to the corresponding wave equations for the scalar amplitudes  (amplitude equations )
 
 
 
