Negative Mixtures 
But why does the present mechanism of bundle trivialization not work for the negative mixtures in an analogous way?

The reason is that the negative-mixture bundle () cannot be embedded into an  bundle with trivial connection  (). This is most easily seen by trying for the principal-bundle section  () the same -valued ansatz  () but with the density vector  being now "space-like", i.e. one takes  for the normalization condition (). This would namely yield for the corresponding pure gauge  ()
 
From here it is immediately seen that one has to take again the group parameter  as a constant over space-time in order that the projection of  onto the holonomy algebra  be zero, cf. (). However one evidently can have no non-trivial value for this constant  so that the decomposition () does apply with both the connection forms  and  obeying the inhomogeneous  law () and  obeying the homogeneous  law ()! This is the true reason why the negative-mixture bundles cannot be embedded into a trivial  bundle, as is the case with the positive-mixture configurations, and therefore we have to look for an even higher-dimensional trivial bundle for the purpose of embedding.

The solution to this problem is obtained by considering a trivial Lorentz bundle over space-time which has the proper Lorentz group  as its structure group. The corresponding Lorentz algebra is easily obtained by simply complementing its  subalgebra, being spanned by the generators  () - (), by three additional generators  which obey the following algebra
 
 
 
